put recite The night was dark and the small pack gathered around a glowing fire, waiting for their Alpha to come out and speak.\; All had gathered to hear his words, everyone in attendance knew there was something coming, but none were sure what it was.\; However, on the fringes of the gathering stood a group of smaller Rakash, sitting just at the edge of the light.\; Their coats black as night, accented in a soft white, their frames more wiry and agile than the bulk of the warriors or hunters.\; They stood with their eyes forward, but their ears listening to everything around them.\; This small gathering knew that whatever was coming, they needed to be ready first.

