put say /softl Each scout simply nodded, there was a reason they were known as klusesana, silence. They moved with stealth and speed, they had their own language, one of gestures and movement." He pauses a moment, accenting his words with a gesture outward, two fingers circling in front of himself. "Their lives dedicated to the safety of the pack, they were the beloved of Mrod, their purpose singular.

pause 10

put recite One of the gathered scouts counted out three, he pointed east, their journey shorter and not as wandering as the one to the west.\; Each of the three nodded and with a silent prayer to their watchful patron the three selected moved east.\; The others gathered and without a word began their journey west.\; The pack knew better than to alert any of the departure and held until they were sure the scouts were away.\; Once enough time had passed each Rakash gathered sunk down and gave their howl, the tone calling the scouts home, wishing them safety on their journey.

pause 15

put say /somberly Though they were loved by Mrod and blessed by their pack, they would not all return as they had left.

