put recite The scouts to the west moved in the night, spread out as individuals, but close enough to quickly close in on any danger they might face.\; They stopped frequently to smell the air, feel the grass, looking for any signs of life in their vicinity.\; As they moved on, they faced little issue until they began hearing loud footsteps. The head of the small gathering gestured and each of them melted into the shadows, ears alert, eyes focused and hands on their blades.\; They sat, quietly waiting for the first sign of trouble when the source of the commotion came into view.\; A pack of Prydaen moved through their path, too many to be a scouting party, wagons loaded and moving at a steady pace through the night.\; The Rakash waited in their shadow knowing the path was no longer viable, too much noise, the wheels leaving clear tracks where they had mapped.\; And so with a heavy sigh the leader motioned for the group to backtrack and scout a new path.

